1. Introduction

Work in progress on Java 7 packages for Debian.

2. Supported Debian versions

None, but it should build on lenny/squeeze/wheezy;)

3. Usage

To create packages on your own:
- apt-get install dpkg-dev
- git clone git://github.com/rraptorr/sun-java6.git --branch oracle-java7 oracle-java7-7.2
- cd sun-java7-7.2
- Download jdk-7u2-linux-i586.tar.gz and jdk-7u2-linux-x64.tar.gz from
  http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html
  (yes, both, no matter which version you will run)
- dpkg-buildpackage -b
- install any missing packages that dpkg-buildpackage complains about
  and repeat
